The paper deals with location-based social networking services and proposes a new family of geo-social group queries with minimum acquaintance constraint. This involves processing spatial and social data, which suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.DB (database), cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.SOC (social and behavioral sciences), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.IR (information retrieval). Among these, cs.DB and cs.SI are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the paper's focus on processing social and spatial data for efficient querying.
